-- Wong Says Achieving Budget Surplus Is the Biggest Priority, Review Says
-- B y   J a m e s   P a t o n
-- 2010-09-23T20:59:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/wong-says-achieving-budget-surplus-is-the-biggest-priority-review-says.html
Australian Finance Minister Penny
Wong said that the government won’t negotiate on getting the
budget back to surplus in 2012-2013, the Australian Financial
Review said, citing the minister.  Wong and Treasurer Wayne Swan said returning the budget to
surplus with a 2 percent spending cap is the government’s top
priority, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
James Paton in Sydney at 
